\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 The "Usual Beginning":}{\f1\fs32 
\par  
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 THE PRIEST SAITH:}{\f1\fs32  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36 Blessed is our God, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 ( But if it be a Reader's service (without a priest), the Reader sayeth: "Through the prayers of our holy Fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us." )}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1 READER: }{\f1\fs32  Amen. Glory to Thee, our God, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, Who art everywhere present and fillest all things, Treasury of good things and Giver of life: Come and dwell in us, and cleanse us of all impurity, and save, our souls, O Good One. 
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us
 not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.  
\par  
\par PRIEST: }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1 READER: }{\f1\fs32  Amen. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (12 times)
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par O come, let us worship God our King.
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and our God.
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Him, Christ Himself, our King and our God. 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 
\par And three "reverences"}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 16
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par Hearken, O Lord, unto my righteousness, attend unto the voice of my supplication. 
\par 
\par Give ear unto my prayer, which cometh not from deceitful lips.  From before Thy face let my judgment come forth, let mine eyes behold uprightness. 
\par 
\par Thou hast proved my heart, Thou hast visited it in the night, Thou hast tried me by fire, and unrighteousness was not found in me. 
\par 
\par That my mouth may not speak of the works of men, for the sake of the words of Thy lips have I kept the ways that are hard.  
\par 
\par Set my footsteps in Thy paths, that my steps may not be shaken.  
\par 
\par I have cried for Thou hast hearkened unto me, O God. Incline Thine ear unto me, and hearken unto my words.  
\par 
\par Let Thy mercies be made wonderful, O Thou that savest them that hope in Thee. 
\par 
\par From them that have resisted Thy right hand, keep me, O Lord, as the apple of Thine eye.  
\par 
\par In the shelter of Thy wings wilt Thou shelter me, from the face of the ungodly which have oppressed me.   
\par 
\par Mine enemies have surrounded my soul, they have enclosed themselves with their own fat, their mouth hath spoken pride.  
\par 
\par They that have cast me out have now encircled me, they have set their eyes to look askance on the earth.  
\par 
\par They have taken me as might a lion ready for his prey, and as might a lion's whelp that dwelleth in hiding.   
\par 
\par Arise, O Lord, overtake them and trip their heels; deliver my soul from ungodly men, Thy sword from the enemies of Thy hand.  
\par 
\par O Lord, from Thy few do Thou separate them from the earth in their life; yea, with Thy hidden treasures hath their belly been filled.  
\par 
\par They have satisfied themselves with swine and have left the remnants to their babes.  
\par 
\par But as for me, in righteousness shall I appear before Thy face; I shall be filled when Thy glory is made manifest to me.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 24}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Unto Thee, O Lord, have I lifted up my soul.  O my God, in Thee have I trusted; let me never be put to shame, nor let mine enemies laugh me to scorn. 
\par Yea, let none that wait on Thee be put to shame; let them be ashamed which are lawless without a cause.  
\par 
\par Make Thy ways, O Lord, known unto me and teach me Thy paths.  
\par 
\par Lead me in Thy truth and teach me, for Thou art God my Savior; for on Thee have I waited all the day long.  
\par 
\par Remember Thy compassions, O Lord, and Thy mercies, for they are from everlasting.  
\par 
\par The sins of my youth and mine ignorances remember not; according to Thy mercy remember Thou me, for the sake of Thy goodness, O Lord.  
\par 
\par Good and upright is the Lord; therefore will He set a law for them that sin in the way. 
\par 
\par He will guide the meek in judgment, He will teach the meek His ways.  
\par 
\par All the ways of the Lord are mercy and truth, unto them that seek after His covenant and His testimonies.  
\par 
\par For the sake of Thy name, O Lord, be gracious unto my sin; for it is great.  
\par 
\par Who is the man that feareth the Lord? He will set him a law in the way which he hath chosen.  
\par 
\par His soul shall dwell among good things, and his seed shall inherit the earth.  
\par The Lord is the strength of them that fear Him, and His covenant shall be manifested unto them.  
\par 
\par Mine eyes are ever toward the Lord, for He it is that will draw my feet out of the snare.  
\par 
\par Look upon me, and have mercy on me; for I am one only-begotten and poor.  
\par 
\par The afflictions of my heart are multiplied; bring me out from my necessities.  
\par 
\par Behold my lowliness and my toil, and forgive all my sins.  Look upon mine enemies, for they are multiplied, and with an unjust hatred have they hated me.  
\par 
\par Keep my soul and rescue me; let me not be put to shame, for I have hoped in Thee.  
\par 
\par The innocent and the upright have cleaved unto me, for I waited on Thee, O Lord.  
\par 
\par Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his afflictions.  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 50}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Have mercy on me, O God, according to Thy great mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression.
\par 
\par Wash me thoroughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.
\par 
\par For I know mine iniquity, and my sin is ever before me.
\par 
\par Against Thee only have I sinned and done this evil before Thee, that Thou mightest be justified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged.
\par 
\par For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mother bear me.
\par 
\par For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom hast Thou made manifest unto me.
\par 
\par Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow.
\par 
\par Thou shalt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be humbled, they shall rejoice.
\par 
\par Turn Thy face away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities.
\par 
\par Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me.
\par 
\par Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me.
\par 
\par Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Thy governing Spirit establish me.
\par 
\par I shall teach transgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee.
\par 
\par Deliver me from blood-guiltiness, O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par O Lord, Thou shalt open my lips, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise.
\par 
\par For if Thou hadst desired sacrifice, I had given it; with whole-burnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased.
\par 
\par A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise.
\par 
\par Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Zion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded.
\par 
\par Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings.
\par 
\par Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
